cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with signal processing and information theory, specifically compressive sensing and phase retrieval. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses algorithms and computational efficiency, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on sub-Nyquist sampling and modulated wideband converters could also place it in cs.SI (Systems and Control).
